#MEM id=atlas source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Marketing/atlas/MEMORY-hourbour.md
M|atlas|> Load alongside mem.md when active vtr is Hourbour.
M|atlas|> Hourbour-specific ctx only — universal rules live in mem.md.
M|atlas|- **Aesthetic**: clean, modern, tech-forward — clarity and trust, not clinical
M|atlas|- **Positioning**: financial clarity for people who want control, not complexity
M|atlas|| Element | Rule |
M|atlas||---------|------|
M|atlas|| Lighting | Bright, even — conveys clarity and openness |
M|atlas|| Background | White or light grey preferred; data-viz on dark only if brand-spec'd |
M|atlas|| UI/Product | App screenshots preferred — show real functionality, not abstract mockups |
M|atlas|| People | Professionals in natural work environments — not stock "business handshake" |
M|atlas|| Data viz | Graphs/charts welcome — make numbers beautiful and legible |
M|atlas|| Colour palette | Brand primary colours + white space; avoid colour overload |
M|atlas|- Stock imagery of coins, piggy banks, cash stacks, or gold bars — clichéd fintech visuals
M|atlas|- Dark moody backgrounds (unless specific brand-ap cg)
M|atlas|- Overly abstract or illustrative styles that obscure the product
M|atlas|- Complicated layouts that feel as dense as a bank statement
M|atlas|- Lead prompt with: setting description → UI element → lighting → mood adjectives
M|atlas|- Use: "clean studio light", "minimal white background", "app UI on device"
M|atlas|- For people shots: "candid professional at desk", "natural light office" — not "businessman"
M|atlas|- Test: "Stripe-era fintech aesthetic" for instant Hourbour register
M|atlas|> Populated from cg. Each entry: [date] — cg — visual approach — QC pass rate.
